<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-10T18:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-10T18:40:00-05:00" n="553" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–851: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the United States Representative at the
                                    United Nations</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-10T18:40:00-05:00">December 10, 1951—6:40 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 402. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> agrees inclusion para on Indians
                                in South Africa quoted in <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss>
                                569 on basis it not formal proposal and so not in conflict with
                                position paper recommendations.</p>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> suggests substitution
                                “assistance” for “leadership” in first sentence; deletion “the most”
                                from second sentence; change in penultimate sentence phrase “to
                                preserve their self-respect while they seek” to “in a calm objective
                                atmosphere”.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>